            noun</a>.</p>

    <p>Examples of <g>seòmar</g> as the subject of the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"
            ><g>bi</g></a> – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha an seòmar glè bhlàth.</gd>
                                        <tr>The room is very warm.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                            <li>demonstrative – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>A bheil an seòmar seo blàth? Chan eil.</gd>
                                        <tr>Is this room warm? No, it isn’t.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
